payload.plan_json: {"Period 1": {"Topic": "Introduction to Natural Language Processing (NLP)", "Hints": "Discuss the scope, challenges, and applications of NLP. Introduce why NLP is hard and its relationship to linguistics and statistics.", "Resources": "Lecture notes, Jurafsky & Martin Chapter 1, course syllabus overview[3][2]."}, "Period 2": {"Topic": "Probability Concepts in NLP", "Hints": "Cover joint and conditional probability, chain rule, and their role in modeling language sequences.", "Resources": "Jurafsky & Martin Chapter 2, probability calculus review material[2][3]."}, "Period 3": {"Topic": "N-gram Language Models", "Hints": "Explain n-grams, language modeling, and basic sequence modeling. Discuss cross-entropy and perplexity.", "Resources": "Jurafsky & Martin Chapter 3, Bird Chapter 3, lecture slides[3][4][2]."}, "Period 4": {"Topic": "Smoothing Techniques and Applications", "Hints": "Introduce smoothing methods for n-grams (e.g., Laplace, Good-Turing). Apply to tasks like spelling correction and text segmentation.", "Resources": "Jurafsky & Martin Chapters 3-4, Rosenfeld (2000), lecture notes[3][2]."}, "Period 5": {"Topic": "Corpora and Text Preprocessing", "Hints": "Discuss corpus construction, representativeness, tokenization, sentence splitting, and concordances.", "Resources": "Bird Chapter 2, corpus construction guidelines, lecture slides[2][4]."}, "Period 6": {"Topic": "Morphological Analysis and Lexical Resources", "Hints": "Cover stemming, lemmatization, morphological operations, and use of static lexica like WordNet.", "Resources": "Bird Chapter 4, WordNet documentation, lecture notes[4][2]."}, "Period 7": {"Topic": "Syntax: POS Tagging and Parsing", "Hints": "Introduce part-of-speech tagging, grammar formalisms (CFGs, FSAs), and parsing algorithms.", "Resources": "Jurafsky & Martin relevant chapters, parsing worksheet, Bird Chapter 5[3][2][4]."}, "Period 8": {"Topic": "Semantics: Lexical and Distributional Models", "Hints": "Explain lexical semantics, word sense disambiguation, distributional semantics, and embeddings.", "Resources": "FrameNet, WordNet, Jurafsky & Martin semantics chapters, Bird Chapter 6[2][4]."}, "Period 9": {"Topic": "Deep Learning for NLP", "Hints": "Introduce neural networks for NLP, sequence models (RNNs, transformers), and pretraining approaches.", "Resources": "Jurafsky & Martin deep learning chapters, lecture notes, Bird Chapter 7[1][2]."}, "Period 10": {"Topic": "Applications: Classification, Sentiment Analysis, NER, Prompting", "Hints": "Explore downstream NLP tasks: document classification, sentiment analysis, named entity recognition, and prompting with pre-trained models.", "Resources": "Jurafsky & Martin application chapters, Bird application chapters, project guidelines[2][4][1]."}}
